00:12:44.051 --> 00:12:47.188 position:5% line:83% align:start
You get it, Nagisa?
You ARE our dream!

00:12:47.288 --> 00:12:49.791 position:5% line:83% align:start
That's what being
parents is all about!

00:12:49.891 --> 00:12:52.760 position:5% line:83% align:start
That's what being a
family is all about!

00:12:52.860 --> 00:12:55.665 position:5% line:83% align:start
Since then... ever
since that day...

00:12:55.764 --> 00:12:58.435 position:5% line:89% align:start
we've been baking our bread...

00:12:58.535 --> 00:13:02.073 position:5% line:83% align:start
waiting, longing
for today to come!

00:13:02.173 --> 00:13:05.244 position:5% line:83% align:start
If you get discouraged and give
up now, then all our dreams die!

00:13:05.344 --> 00:13:06.945 position:5% line:89% align:start
You got that!?

00:13:07.045 --> 00:13:10.115 position:5% line:83% align:start
This is your responsibility now!
Get it!?

00:13:10.216 --> 00:13:14.053 position:5% line:83% align:start
Sanae, you're here, aren't you?
You tell her, too!

00:13:14.153 --> 00:13:16.523 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Sanae] You can do it, Nagisa!

00:13:17.925 --> 00:13:19.494 position:5% line:89% align:start
What? What's going on?

00:13:19.594 --> 00:13:20.962 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Kyou] Tomoya!
[Kotomi] Huh?

00:13:22.698 --> 00:13:24.533 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Tomoya] The same goes
for us too, Nagisa!

00:13:24.634 --> 00:13:29.206 position:5% line:77% align:start
What you're trying to make
happen right now is what
Sunohara and I couldn't do!

00:13:29.306 --> 00:13:31.141 position:5% line:83% align:start
All of our failures
and frustrations

00:13:31.241 --> 00:13:33.478 position:5% line:83% align:start
are resting on your
shoulders now!

00:13:54.102 --> 00:13:59.842 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Nagisa inhales, then exhales]

00:14:06.584 --> 00:14:08.621 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Nagisa] If you'd like...

00:14:08.721 --> 00:14:11.090 position:5% line:83% align:start
If you'd like,
shall I take you...?

00:14:13.426 --> 00:14:17.699 position:5% line:83% align:start
To the place... in town,
where wishes come true?

00:14:17.799 --> 00:14:19.933 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>[Tomoya] Take us there, Nagisa!</i>

00:14:20.033 --> 00:14:21.436 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>Take all of us.</i>

00:14:22.837 --> 00:14:26.041 position:5% line:83% align:start
This is a world that
has come to an end.

00:14:26.141 --> 00:14:29.346 position:5% line:83% align:start
An empty and still world
where no one exists but I.

00:14:29.446 --> 00:14:33.417 position:5% line:77% align:start
There is small table
and chair in this room,
but outside the window...

00:14:33.517 --> 00:14:38.390 position:5% line:77% align:start
there is nothing but an empty
plain, stretching into an
endless horizon.

00:14:39.624 --> 00:14:40.959 position:5% line:89% align:start
This building is old.

00:14:41.059 --> 00:14:43.429 position:5% line:83% align:start
I don't know how long
ago it was built.

00:14:44.832 --> 00:14:48.000 position:5% line:83% align:start
I live here alone,
passing time in solitude.

00:14:48.102 --> 00:14:53.341 position:5% line:77% align:start
Sometimes I venture outside,
picking up little odds and
ends that I might need.

00:14:55.910 --> 00:14:58.647 position:5% line:83% align:start
Of course, there is no
one outside, either...

00:14:58.748 --> 00:15:03.387 position:5% line:77% align:start
but under the fading sun,
a sea of tiny lights are
fluttering about.

00:15:05.222 --> 00:15:07.992 position:5% line:83% align:start
Amidst those lights,
I picked up wood scraps,

00:15:08.092 --> 00:15:10.161 position:5% line:89% align:start
nails and many other things.

00:15:10.261 --> 00:15:12.965 position:5% line:83% align:start
My purpose was to
create a friend.

00:15:13.065 --> 00:15:15.368 position:5% line:83% align:start
But now... even as
I construct him,

00:15:15.468 --> 00:15:19.172 position:5% line:77% align:start
I wonder if anyone would be
happy to be born in a
world like this.

00:15:19.272 --> 00:15:23.177 position:5% line:83% align:start
At every turn, those feelings
of doubt still haunt me.

00:15:26.114 --> 00:15:29.218 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>[Voice] This world indeed</i>
 <i>has come to an end.</i>

00:15:29.318 --> 00:15:32.054 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>It will not give birth</i>
 <i>to another life.</i>

00:15:32.155 --> 00:15:36.628 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>This girl is the only living</i>
 <i>creature that remains.</i>

00:15:36.728 --> 00:15:41.099 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Sometime long ago... or perhaps</i>
 <i>in the distant future...</i>

00:15:41.199 --> 00:15:43.636 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>I was in a different world.</i>

00:15:43.736 --> 00:15:46.272 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>It was a world full of life.</i>

00:15:46.372 --> 00:15:49.209 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>But I can no longer</i>
 <i>return to that place.</i>

00:15:49.309 --> 00:15:53.882 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>Because now I exist inside this</i>
 <i>body that she made for me.</i>

00:15:53.981 --> 00:15:55.450 position:5% line:89% align:start
What's the matter?

00:15:57.084 --> 00:15:59.188 position:5% line:89% align:start
Should I... make another?

00:16:01.957 --> 00:16:05.128 position:5% line:83% align:start
But why? It won't
be able to move.

00:16:05.228 --> 00:16:08.365 position:5% line:83% align:start
We can't do it.
We can't make friends.

00:16:11.303 --> 00:16:13.972 position:5% line:83% align:start
But you don't want me to
make a friend this time?

00:16:16.576 --> 00:16:17.845 position:5% line:89% align:start
Something else?

00:16:17.945 --> 00:16:21.682 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>[Voice] I don't know what,</i>
 <i>but we have to make something.</i>

00:16:21.782 --> 00:16:27.489 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>She can create something</i>
 <i>new from junk parts...</i>
 <i>just like she created me.</i>

00:16:27.589 --> 00:16:31.293 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>We can't let that special</i>
 <i>gift of her's go to waste.</i>

00:16:32.061 --> 00:16:33.396 position:5% line:89% align:start
Yeah, you're right.

00:16:33.497 --> 00:16:35.332 position:5% line:83% align:start
If we try hard enough,
with time,

00:16:35.432 --> 00:16:38.503 position:5% line:83% align:start
we may be able to make
something truly wonderful.

00:16:41.405 --> 00:16:43.308 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well what shall we make then?

00:16:46.512 --> 00:16:47.647 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Girl gasp]

00:16:48.214 --> 00:16:49.649 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Girl giggles]

00:16:49.749 --> 00:16:52.553 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>[Voice] Something that</i>
 <i>will make my heart leap!</i>

00:16:52.653 --> 00:16:55.456 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>She'll make it...</i>
 <i>and I can help her.</i>

00:16:55.556 --> 00:16:59.294 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>That, in itself,</i>
 <i>is a wonderful thing.</i>

00:16:59.394 --> 00:17:03.165 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'll stay by her side,</i>
 <i>doing whatever I can.</i>

00:17:03.266 --> 00:17:06.570 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>We'll be together forever.</i>
 <i>And one day,</i>

00:17:06.670 --> 00:17:08.940 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>the two of us will</i>
 <i>leave this place.</i>

00:17:09.039 --> 00:17:14.245 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>Then we'll travel to the</i>
 <i>warm and beautiful world</i>
 <i>that I once lived in.</i>

00:17:15.347 --> 00:17:17.683 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Audience applauding]

00:17:29.096 --> 00:17:31.400 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Nagisa] I remembered the rest.
[Tomoya] Hm?

00:17:31.500 --> 00:17:33.503 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Nagisa] The rest of
the story, I mean.

00:17:33.603 --> 00:17:36.040 position:5% line:83% align:start
Eventually, the girl and
the little doll decide

00:17:36.139 --> 00:17:38.475 position:5% line:83% align:start
to leave that sad
and empty world behind.

00:17:38.576 --> 00:17:41.545 position:5% line:83% align:start
'Cause the little doll knew
that somewhere, far, far away,

00:17:41.645 --> 00:17:43.748 position:5% line:83% align:start
there was another world
for them to live in.

00:17:43.848 --> 00:17:45.818 position:5% line:89% align:start
One full of warmth and life.

00:17:45.918 --> 00:17:47.787 position:5% line:89% align:start
So what happens then?

00:17:47.887 --> 00:17:51.725 position:5% line:83% align:start
They set out on a long, long
journey... and at the end

00:17:51.825 --> 00:17:53.226 position:5% line:89% align:start
And at the end?

00:17:53.327 --> 00:17:54.661 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Nagisa] They sing a song.

00:17:55.629 --> 00:17:56.464 position:5% line:89% align:start
You serious?

00:17:56.564 --> 00:17:57.565 position:5% line:89% align:start
Of course I am.

00:17:57.665 --> 00:17:59.434 position:5% line:83% align:start
They sing a song at the
end of the journey,

00:17:59.534 --> 00:18:01.570 position:5% line:83% align:start
so I sang a song at
the end of the play.

00:18:01.670 --> 00:18:03.772 position:5% line:83% align:start
Why else do you think I would
do something like that?

00:18:03.873 --> 00:18:06.076 position:5% line:83% align:start
All right, I'll give you that,
but I doubt she would've

00:18:06.175 --> 00:18:08.111 position:5% line:89% align:start
sang the Big Dango Family song.

00:18:08.211 --> 00:18:10.113 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, no, that part was just me.

00:18:10.213 --> 00:18:11.616 position:5% line:83% align:start
I know everyone
applauded and all,

00:18:11.716 --> 00:18:14.485 position:5% line:83% align:start
but I think they were a little
confused by the ending.

00:18:14.586 --> 00:18:18.390 position:5% line:83% align:start
That song kind of ruined the
whole emotional build up.

00:18:18.490 --> 00:18:21.294 position:5% line:83% align:start
I just really wanted
to sing it, that's all.

00:18:23.596 --> 00:18:25.399 position:5% line:89% align:start
Well, whatever.

00:18:25.499 --> 00:18:27.936 position:5% line:83% align:start
Other than the song,
the play was great.

00:18:28.036 --> 00:18:29.269 position:5% line:89% align:start
Do you really mean it?

00:18:29.371 --> 00:18:30.872 position:5% line:89% align:start
I never flatter people.

00:18:30.972 --> 00:18:32.140 position:5% line:89% align:start
You know that.

00:18:32.240 --> 00:18:33.609 position:5% line:89% align:start
Yeah, I do.

00:18:33.709 --> 00:18:36.445 position:5% line:83% align:start
That's why I was surprised
to hear you say that.

00:18:41.418 --> 00:18:43.921 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Nagisa] I'm glad
to see you came.

00:18:44.022 --> 00:18:46.959 position:5% line:89% align:start
I got an invitation, after all.

00:18:47.059 --> 00:18:50.329 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm sorry if I was out of
line by telling him... but...

00:18:50.429 --> 00:18:53.299 position:5% line:83% align:start
I thought he should know what
was going on at least.

00:18:53.400 --> 00:18:55.102 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Naoyuki] I saw the
play this afternoon.

00:18:55.201 --> 00:18:56.604 position:5% line:89% align:start
It was a wonderful story.

00:18:56.704 --> 00:18:58.939 position:5% line:89% align:start
Thank you very much.

00:18:59.041 --> 00:19:02.411 position:5% line:83% align:start
It made me think a lot about
the past, in a good way.

00:19:06.281 --> 00:19:08.618 position:5% line:83% align:start
Well, I suppose I
should be going now.

00:19:08.718 --> 00:19:10.319 position:5% line:89% align:start
Okay.

00:19:11.121 --> 00:19:12.623 position:5% line:89% align:start
Don't drink too much, all right?

00:19:12.723 --> 00:19:13.858 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Naoyuki gasp]

00:19:19.965 --> 00:19:21.434 position:5% line:89% align:start
Hey, Okazaki...?

00:19:24.437 --> 00:19:26.506 position:5% line:83% align:start
Listen, you wanna go
somewhere with me tomorrow?

00:19:26.606 --> 00:19:29.143 position:5% line:77% align:start
[Nagisa] Huh?
[Tomoya] It's a three-day
weekend, right?

00:19:29.242 --> 00:19:31.212 position:5% line:83% align:start
It'd be nice if it
was just us two.

00:19:31.312 --> 00:19:32.981 position:5% line:83% align:start
There's something
I wanna talk about.

00:19:33.082 --> 00:19:34.049 position:5% line:83% align:start
[Nagisa] Talk about?
[Kyou] Ah ha!

00:19:34.149 --> 00:19:35.417 position:5% line:89% align:start
[Kyou] So there you are!

00:19:35.517 --> 00:19:37.053 position:5% line:83% align:start
Everyone's waiting
in the club room.

00:19:37.153 --> 00:19:40.824 position:5% line:83% align:start
We can't start the party without
the director and the big star!

00:19:40.924 --> 00:19:42.093 position:5% line:89% align:start
Sorry 'bout that.

00:19:42.193 --> 00:19:43.861 position:5% line:89% align:start
Let's go.

00:19:43.961 --> 00:19:45.296 position:5% line:89% align:start
Okay!

00:20:06.722 --> 00:20:09.793 position:5% line:11% align:start
Don't we need to get
permission to go inside
the school like this?

00:20:09.893 --> 00:20:13.363 position:5% line:11% align:start
[Tomoya] Whatever,
we're students here,
so I'm sure it's fine.

00:20:13.463 --> 00:20:14.899 position:5% line:17% align:start
[Nagisa] I guess you're right.

00:20:17.735 --> 00:20:20.005 position:5% line:17% align:start
[Tomoya] Yanno, lately...
[Nagisa] Hm?

00:20:20.105 --> 00:20:23.609 position:5% line:11% align:start
Lately, I've been starting
to feel like this school
isn't so bad after all.

00:20:23.709 --> 00:20:26.846 position:5% line:17% align:start
Well, is that so? I'm happy
to hear you say that.

00:20:27.948 --> 00:20:30.951 position:5% line:17% align:start
Huh? I'm the class monitor?!
Since when?

00:20:31.051 --> 00:20:34.122 position:5% line:11% align:start
[Tomoya] Oh yeah, I put
that up there as a joke
when you were absent.

00:20:34.222 --> 00:20:35.390 position:5% line:17% align:start
Forgot about that.

00:20:35.490 --> 00:20:38.027 position:5% line:17% align:start
And all this time
I never noticed it.

00:20:39.262 --> 00:20:40.596 position:5% line:17% align:start
Hm...

00:20:52.244 --> 00:20:54.914 position:27% line:71% align:start
 There, we're even now.
  [giggles]

00:20:55.282 --> 00:20:56.615 position:5% line:71% align:start
Ah!

00:20:59.786 --> 00:21:02.523 position:5% line:71% align:start
I said before that we had
something to talk about...

00:21:02.623 --> 00:21:04.759 position:5% line:71% align:start
Yeah? Is something
on your mind?

00:21:04.860 --> 00:21:08.664 position:5% line:11% align:start
[Tomoya] Well, uh... I'm
not sure how to say this.
[Nagisa] Hm?

00:21:12.368 --> 00:21:15.072 position:5% line:77% align:start
Uh... Wouldn't it be funny...

00:21:15.172 --> 00:21:18.709 position:5% line:71% align:start
if we woke up tomorrow and we
were boyfriend and girlfriend?

00:21:18.809 --> 00:21:19.945 position:5% line:77% align:start
Huh?

00:21:25.417 --> 00:21:27.854 position:5% line:77% align:start
Will you go out with me, Nagisa?

00:21:28.588 --> 00:21:30.257 position:5% line:77% align:start
I love you, Nagisa.

00:21:30.356 --> 00:21:34.629 position:5% line:11% align:start
So I... I want to spend
every day of my life
together with you.

00:23:44.220 --> 00:23:48.557 position:5% line:77% align:start
Oh, I forgot to tell you,
Okazaki said he was going
over to Sunohara's.

00:23:48.658 --> 00:23:50.495 position:5% line:89% align:start
What is it, Okazaki?

00:23:50.594 --> 00:23:54.732 position:5% line:77% align:start
Lately...I've had these thoughts
about you that I just can't
get out of my head.

00:23:54.832 --> 00:23:56.168 position:5% line:89% align:start
Seem to be enjoying themselves.

00:23:56.268 --> 00:23:59.104 position:5% line:83% align:start
If I ask, do you think
they'll let me join in maybe?

00:23:59.204 --> 00:24:01.673 position:5% line:83% align:start
There's nobody around,
don't worry about it.

00:24:01.775 --> 00:24:03.743 position:5% line:83% align:start
You tell her, kid.
You know what I'm saying.

00:24:03.843 --> 00:24:05.545 position:5% line:89% align:start
What, are you in grade school?

00:24:05.645 --> 00:24:06.747 position:5% line:89% align:start
All right, then...

00:24:06.847 --> 00:24:08.483 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'll just have
to tell her myself.

00:24:08.582 --> 00:24:10.819 position:5% line:83% align:start
Man, that's getting
me worked up!

